column11:
Tollhouse Preschool was organized in 1985 to provide quality childcare for children.  We are conveniently located in Merrimack, NH right off exit 11.  The program serves children 6 weeks to 12 years old and is fully licensed through the NH Bureau of Child Care Standards and Licensing.

Tollhouse Preschool is dedicated to offering a safe, nurturing, and engaging environment for children to learn.  Our programs are developmentally appropriate and encourage children to freely explore their environment.  Our staff is well-trained and educated and creates an environment that encourages children to develop socially, physically, and intellectually.

We cater to the individual needs of each child and parent
-We are a developmental preschool- children are never rushed or held back because of age
The center is equipped with a security system
Classrooms are monitored by surveillance cameras
Doors are secured with a pass code system
Our youngest friends enjoy a separate, age appropriate outside play area
Several times throughout the year we host after school family events
We are conveniently located next to the Park and Ride and 1/2 a mile from Exit 5 on Interstate 93

The Early Learning Center of Milford (ELCM) was created with the young child in mind.  Our nurturing staff believes in fostering a positive self-image and a feeling of success in each and every child.

 Our classrooms and outdoor environments are rich in materials and provide direct and concrete experiences for all learners.

Our social curriculum facilitates positive social interactions, fosters independent thinkers, and develops problem solving skills.

Our academic programming is developmentally appropriate and encourages a positive attitude towards learning.

Our extended day options provide flexibility to meet the needs of working parents.

The Early Learning Center of Milford is licensed by the State of New Hampshire and is owned and operated by certified teachers.  Together, the owners bring forward over 50 years of combined knowledge and experience.

Our comprehensive path for the young child begins at 13 months in our Toddler program, leads into our Preschool program, continues through our Pre-Kindergarten program, and is completed at age six in our full-day Kindergarten program.

Little Arrows Child Care Services is a non-profit organization whose mission is to provide quality child care services and early learning programs based on Christian principles and standards with the intent of fostering in each child a loving attitude, respect for themselves and others, and positive character development.

Little Arrows is a licensed child care and early learning center. We provide a well balanced program of activities and developmentally appropriate curriculum to foster all areas of growth and development, serving the communities of Southern New Hampshire with high quality care.

Play has been called the work of a child. Some adults consider play as something frivolous and a complete waste of time. But, to the young child, play is very serious business requiring deep concentration. Play is a time to be absorbed in painting a picture, building with blocks or being a “Grandfather” in a dramatic play area. The feelings are earnest and intense.
A child engrossed in play is a lot like an adult working on a project he/she loves or an artist enthralled in their creation.

Play is a time for thinking, a time to solve problems and a time to investigate. Play is a time to organize thoughts. Play is a time to use mind and body, along with the social skills possessed, to respond to an idea or situation.

Play is a time to learn from each other and learn about the world in which they live!

The “work time” element of our curriculum has a playful quality as describes above. Children work individually or in small groups and flow from task to task. The teacher’s role is to provide challenging stimulus and expand upon the child’s learning, guiding their development. As the children “play/work” teachers are busy hearing what they say, “reading” each child’s face and sensing what is on their minds. The observations create the agenda for future plans with the children as individuals and as a group.

 Our Staff has 20 Plus Years of Preschool and Childcare Experience. Our teachers are Early Childhood Degreed and Certified. All staff members are CPR and 1st Aid Certified. We teach a developmentally appropriate curriculum.

Southern New Hampshire Services, Inc. (SNHS) is a private non-profit corporation chartered in the State of New Hampshire, May 21, 1965 to serve as the Community Action Agency for Hillsborough County in compliance with the Economic Opportunity Act of 1964.

From 1965 through 1969, SNHS was known as the Community Action Agency for Hillsborough County and served the City of Nashua and the twenty-nine towns.  In 1969 the organization became the Community Action Agency for the City of Manchester as well.  In 1974 the agency’s name was changed to Southern New Hampshire Services, Inc.

In July, 2011, Rockingham Community Action (RCA), the Community Action Agency serving Rockingham County, was merged with Southern New Hampshire Services.  SNHS had served as the administrative agent for RCA since October, 2008.  As a result of this merger SNHS now provides services to residents all 65 towns and three cities in Hillsborough and Rockingham counties.

Humpty Dumpty Learning Center offers care to children ages six weeks through six years old. We focus on constant interactions between children and teachers. Our program stresses the learning through play philosophy because we believe children learn best with hands-on activities and experience. Our basic philosophy is to help your child in all phases of his/her growth, physically, emotionally, and intellectually. And most importantly by helping them to develop a positive self image. We believe that children are a gift shared with us for a short time, to be loved, cared for, and respected for the little miracles they are. We do not take lightly the trust you have placed in our school, in the education and the care of your child.

Our mission and passion is to help girls achieve their personal best through one-on-one attention, leadership development, a talented staff and volunteers, a wide range of enrichment programs, and a caring family environment.

Almost Angels is a small, in-home, state-licensed preschool program where learning is fun! Your child will benefit from having small class sizes by getting more personal attention, more hands on experience, closer bonds with teacher and friends and overall better quality of care.

The main goals of preschool are to have fun, improve social skills, develop self-esteem, and encourage creative expression. A variety of activities are utilized to accomplish these goals: reading, arts & crafts, music & singing, dancing, dramatic play, puzzles, water exploration, sensory play, etc. This will not be a rigorous academic program as young children learn best through play!

Almost Angels has a large indoor area for the children to move freely. The room is very bright and cheerful with plenty of hands on equipment as well as a variety of play materials. Child size furniture and plenty of art and craft supplies are on hand for the children to explore daily.

Outside is a large play area with swings, slides, climbers, sandbox, riding toys, and plenty of room to run and have fun with friends.

I feel truly rewarded to work with children on a daily basis. I love my job very much and get great pleasure in seeing the children head off to school. It is such a wonderful feeling knowing I had such an impact on a child's life. Almost Angels Preschool offers a wonderful environment for the children to develop and grow. I provide the highest quality care of children and achieve this through experience, education and my love for children.

Welcome to The Goddard School! Our goal is to be a resource for families and a community where parents can share information and learn from each other.  The Goddard School uses the most current, academically endorsed methods to ensure that children have fun while learning the skills they need for long-term success in school and in life. Our talented teachers also collaborate with parents to nurture children into respectful, confident and joyful learners.

column11: White Wing School is committed to providing a quality educational experience for preschool and kindergarten age children. We place great importance on the development of the whole child by creating an environment that nurtures the individual child’s intellect, emotional development, creativity and physical gifts in order to foster a lifelong love of learning.

We are a non-profit Preschool based in Nashua, New Hampshire and we provide an educational and play environment to children ages 3 and 4 years old with the goal to assist them in the learning process in all aspects that is necessary to prepare them for their elementary school years. We are a non-denominational, non-sectarian Pre-Nursery and Nursery school environment and is non discriminatory in our admissions and hiring practices.

Our Preschool is dedicated to providing a warm and safe surrounding to the young minds while allowing them to explore at their own pace and with guided counselling and help from the friendly teachers and their assistants in all categories from early recognition of literary materials, development of social and teamwork skills and constructive play and art appreciation.

The goal of the Little People's Depot preschool program is to help each child grow physically, intellectually and socially.  The child's emotional and social development is of primary importance.  The teachers help the children grow in these areas by:

    Encouraging active curiosity and enthusiasm for learning
    Providing opportunities to learn new information and develop increasingly complex problem solving skills﻿                 
    Creating an atmosphere that recognizes children's feelings, ideas and attitudes and helps them express these in constructive and meaningful ways.
    Encouraging each child to develop a positive self-image, which enables him/her to function comfortably in a group situation.
    Supporting individual creative expression.
    Providing opportunities for children to use their growing bodies to develop skill and coordination.
    Promoting cooperative social interactions with children and adults.

﻿

Our Mission at Strong Beginnings is to cater to the whole child, by providing a safe and nurturing environment. Our center has a diverse curriculum that nurtures the arts throughout all academic areas, guiding children on the path of literacy and creativity. The staff encourages each child at his/her individual development stage.

Our goal today remains the same: building a partnership with parents; linking home with school while providing a loving, secure environment that is enriching to all - children, parents and teachers.


Our mission: To continually strive to be “The Perfect Place” for your child.  A place to spend “Quality Time” in a nurturing, enriching environment with “Endless Opportunities” to grow, while developing “Dynamic Foundations” for successful living and learning!!

We understand that trying to choose someone to take care of your child is stressful. Kimba's kids has an open door policy at all times. Meaning you do not need an appointment to come see us just stop on in anytime and check us out. After you have enrolled with us you are welcome to visit with your child/children anytime before your actual start date to get to know the staff that your child/children will be spending their day with. We have found this to be a very important step in making your first day at Kimba's Kids a much smoother one. You will feel as if your leaving your most valuable possessions with family. Our center provides a safe, fun environment for your child to develope to his or her full potential.

We want to promote personal development of your children to prepare them as best we can for the challenges that lie ahead in life. Our staff consists of experienced, certified and continually trained educators.

Kings Kids Child Care Center, along with the New England Pentecostal Ministries Church, is committed to providing a safe, nurturing and stimulating environment in which children become critical and creative lifelong learners.  We believe that each child is a unique individual and all children are valuable. In the environment of Christian love and values, our dedicated staff will provide an atmosphere that encourages all children to grow and develop while having fun.

Pelham School Age Child Care provides a safe, affordable place for children to go when parents are working or otherwise unavailable. The program creates a unique opportunity within an informal learning environment to enhance a child’s self-esteem and individuality. A variety of developmentally appropriate activities are provided to include a balance of structured and unstructured time as well as staff-directed and child-initiated experiences. A range of activity options includes outdoor play, sports, arts and crafts, games, help with homework, cooking, films (G and PG rated), and free-time. Pelham School Age Child Care is committed to providing quality care for the children of Pelham were a child can find a “home away from home.”

Welcome to Play Laugh N’ Grow Childcare & Pre-school Center. We currently have two locations, one in Raymond, NH and our new location opening soon at 184 raymond rd, Chester, NH. Our goal is to provide a safe, happy, and nurturing environment for your child to learn and grow throughout their younger years. Our program encourages physical, emotional and intellectual development, as well as instilling a love of learning! Each classroom is bright and cheerful, with many of the essential tools to promote learning with a teacher that will nurture and guide your child to become an independent and thoughtful learner! Play Laugh N' grow is a childcare and Pre-school  that was founded by Kristy and Kevin DeCesare in August of 2009. Play Laugh N' Grow provides high quality child care for children, ages 6 weeks to 6 years. We have established a developmentally appropriate curriculum for early education through programs that offer intellectually challenging experiences, and many opportunities to develop social relationships. From the moment you enter our school, its unique atmosphere is evident. Here at Play Laugh N' Grow we have created an environment where learning is a process – a series of experiences beginning the very first moment your child enters our center, whether they be six weeks old, or six years!

Wonder Years Learning Center
was established in 1996 with the idea of providing a safe, learning environment for children. Our goal is to simply help children develop the academic and social skills needed for a successful life.

Our learning centers are designed and equipped to meet the standards of (NAEYC) National Association for the Education of Young Children.

Our teachers are dedicated professionals committed to providing your child quality care, early education, positive modeling and love. Our teachers create a warm caring environment that helps foster each child’s self esteem. Our teachers work closely with parents to guide them through these exciting times in their child’s life.

Wonder Years is proud to provide hundreds of children with quality child care and the love of learning.

column2: Here We Grow Learning Center Of Salem
column11:
Mission Statement
Our goal as child care providers lies within the context of our name, “Here We Grow”. The
title goes beyond a “catchy phrase.” At every age, your child is undergoing momentous
changes physically, emotionally and cognitively. Our goal is to enhance that process with
guidance and direction. With patience and understanding, we hope to introduce them to
the life skills they need to develop to their fullest potential

“Here We Grow” is all about the growth process and helping your child reach
developmental milestones.  As providers and parents ourselves, we are aware that
childrearing is a process and that you are growing and learning along with your child.

Through a warm, open atmosphere, we are available to you whenever you have a
question or to simply be that support system you may need. We are here to fully meet
your needs as well as your child.

Our plan is to provide a safe and diverse environment, geared to guide you and your child  through these wonderful and exciting times

ABOUT US: Little Scholars has been providing quality child care for more than 30 years. We are a licensed Child Care Center and School in the State of New Hampshire.


DAYCARE/SCHOOL PROGRAMS: Little Scholars has Infant and Toddler Care as well as Preschool, Pre-K, Kindergarten and Before and After Care and Summer Camp for School Age children.


TEACHERS: Our qualified and gifted teachers are invested and passionate about teaching children and participate in continuous training and education courses. The are dedicated to providing each child the personalized attention they need to succeed. Many of our teachers have more than 10 years of experience and have taught at Little Scholars for years.


FACILITY: Little Scholars Facility goes beyond our 11 spacious, fully equipped classrooms. We have a full sized, year round, gymnasium for all-season play and exercise, a large outdoor space and playground and an aftercare room that encourages creativity and fun. Our facility grounds are set far away from the main road to enable us to enjoy walks on our grounds.


SAFETY: A safe and secure environment is top priority. We have an access control lock and a video surveillance system we are able to monitor our facilities around the clock.

Joanna Vorce is the Lead Teacher and Director of Salem Kid Start Kindergarten.  She has served at Salem Christian School for the last 21 years overseeing the preschool program as well as teaching the kindergarten students there.  

When Salem Christian School made the decision to close, her passion was to continue to provide quality Christian education for early learners.  In opening her own center, Joanna will continue to build off of her more than 30 years of experience with preschool children.  Her goal is to provide them with engaging opportunities to learn within a loving, Christian environment.  

Joanna has three adult children of her own and resides with her husband Jeffrey Vorce in Windham, NH.

At Merrimack Valley Montessori School (MVMS) individuality is respected and safe-guarded.  Dr. Maria Montessori described the years from two and one-half to six as a "sensitive period". During this period your child is capable of more learning than at any other time in his/her life. If a child is guided intelligently, learning becomes a joyful experience. The 'inner discipline', which a child acquires through his/her exposure to both physical and mental order in the classroom, is the core of the Montessori philosophy. Our aim is the development of each child's full potential in a prepared environment where children can discover for themselves and work independently at their own pace.

Welcome to Create & Discover Learning Center, Inc.  Here at Create & Discover, our guiding principle is to deal fairly and professionally with our parents, children and employees. As a parent you are a very important part of our organization. Your satisfaction with our work and dedication are the foundation for the continued growth and success of your children.

We are here to make a positive impact on the growing abilities and talents of students. We believe in providing the best program possible for our children and their parents and we continually strive to achieve and maintain standards of quality.

We strive to create mutual respect between parents and teachers; a partnership for the benefit of the child. We encourage daily communication between parents and center staff. Our doors are open to parents at all times.

We value the children in our care, their parents and our employees. We continually work to earn the trust placed in us. We strive to be the best provider of early childhood education services in our community.

column2: Salem Boys And Girls Club Preschool
column11:
Kindergarten Enrichment Program is designed to meet the needs of working parents and to complement the Salem School District’s Kindergarten program. We provide early morning care, transportation and after school care. Snow day and vacation day care is available to participants of this program! Please contact Cynthia McKeon for more information.

Extended Day Program offers those students either in the afternoon or full-day public kindergarten care until 6PM. We provide transportation and offer a fun, safe environment inclusive of our new drama program The Positive Players.

The Salem Boys and Girls Club Preschool is a non-profit preschool serving children 3-6 years of age, and is licensed by the State of New Hampshire Department of Health and Welfare.

Our goal at Littleville Learning Center is to provide a safe, comfortable and stimulating environment in which children can learn, grow and have fun. We acknowledge that every child is unique and develops at his/her own pace; therefore each child is cared for as an individual. Our interactive hands on activities are designed to help children make the connection between learning and the world around them. Our program focuses on the whole child to ensure that every child is given the opportunity to grow:

    Physically: Each day children are given the chance to run, jump and stretch in our indoor gymnasium or outdoor playground. We encourage good hygiene, promote healthy eating habits and teach safety.
    Intellectually: All activities that are made available for children throughout the day are intended to enhance language development, problem solving skills and creativity.
    Emotionally/Socially: Children are encouraged to interact with their peers, make their own choices use their imagination and try new things. Our program gives children the ability to succeed while building independence, self-esteem and self-control.

Our experienced teachers are continuously furthering their education of early childhood development to ensure the best for our families and children. We encourage parents to actively participate in our program and look forward to working with families throughout the year.

As early childhood educators it is our intention to support an enthusiasm and love for learning that will provide the foundation for academic success and lifelong skills!

column11: Patsy's house was established in 1996. Patsy's House is a family owned and operated center for children ages 6 weeks to 12 years old. We are licensed through the State of New Hampshire and can accomodate 35 children. Our motto, "Just like home," was created in hopes that the children will feel as though they are coming to their second home.

It is very important to treat every child and family individually to best meet their needs for a school program. Our philosophy views each child as a unique person with an individual pattern and timing of growth. Curriculum and instruction are responsive to individual differences in ability and interests. Different levels of ability, development and learning styles are expected, accepted and used to design curriculum..

With more than 30 years of experience, Champions is a leading provider of high-quality programs for before- and after-school learning and break time camps. Every day, Champions provides fun, learning experiences to more than 15,000 students at over 400 sites in 17 states.

We are recognized for our leadership in delivering extended learning programs that are tailored specifically to a school’s needs and approved by busy working parents who want a safe, convenient program where their child can grow and learn.

Champions is a member of the Knowledge Universe family of education companies. Knowledge Universe is the leading private provider of early childhood and school-age education, serving 200,000 children in 39 states. Champions, through its affiliation with Knowledge Universe, delivers local learning programs backed by the resources and expertise of one of the world’s largest education companies.

I bring you a warm welcome to the Kindertree Learning Center, located in the Sally Zyla Dance Studio building at 162 Manchester Street, Manchester, NH founded in 2004. It is owned and operated by Sally Zyla Addison. I like to think of the Kindertree Learning Center as a place that children and adults consider their second home. A place where all are accepted. A place where laughter and play are cherished. A place where children's rhythms are caught and given a warm response.

Our staff, here at the center, were selected for their knowledge of child development as well as their strong interpersonal skills, they are the strength of our program. When visiting our center, please take time to listen, watch, and learn. You will be enriched.

It is my role and the role of staff to not only facilitate the learning of children, parents, and one another, but to provide quality care in an environment that is safe, nurturing, stimulating, and full of learning experiences that will help your child develop their independence and help build self esteem. We at the Kindertree Learning Center are pleased to embrace these roles and are looking forward to establishing a trusting relationship with each child and their families.
column14: Monday through Friday from 7:30 am - 5:30 pm

column11: Kindertree Learning Center is here to service the children of the Greater Manchester area and beyond. We provide care for children ages 2 years 9 months to 5 years old. We offer Full-Time and Part-Time as well as Full-Day and Part-Day programs. Our Philosophy at Kindertree Learning Center is that children learn best in an environment where they feel physically and emotionally safe. Our main priority is to meet the developmental needs of each child. Developmental areas include social, emotional, physical, and cognitive skills. We will achieve this by observing and interacting on a daily basis with your child as well as working closely and communicating with their families. We will provide a variety of experiences based on the interest and development of each child as an individual and the group of children as a whole Our services stretch beyond child care to support the whole family with daily communication on their child's day, prompt attention to concerns, and parent-teacher conferences upon request.

column2: Little Rising Stars Child Care Center

column11:
At the Elliot Child Care Center, our number one goal is to provide your children with a safe, nurturing environment, in which they are allowed to grow and develop at their own pace.

Curriculum topics, ideas, and activities for all children are developed based on common interests of the children, staff, and families we serve. We believe in a child-centered philosophy in which we encourage and promote social/emotional, physical, and cognitive development through a variety of learning opportunities, including early literacy, science, math, art, music and movement, and dramatic play. Each classroom bases interactions, environment, and curriculum on developmentally appropriate practice for the ages served.

As child advocates, we respect each child as an individual. We appreciate that all children learn through a variety of ways, and that each is developing at their own pace. We believe that family is the most important factor on a young child’s development, and we acknowledge and respect the many forms of diversity that each family brings to our school community.

The staff at Elliot Child Care strongly encourages family involvement throughout the year. We offer many opportunities to share ideas and opinions, including parent meetings, parent conferences, and day-to-day communication. We believe that parent-teacher communication is essential to positive experiences that children will have while they are with us.

The staff of Elliot Child Care Center is committed to a program of enrichment and development through continuing education, in order to provide the best care possible for your child.

column11: At Little Frogs and Polliwogs, we pride ourselves on the professionalism of our staff. Many of our Lead Teachers are degreed teachers, who, along with other staff members, continue their education by taking college courses and attending workshops. Each staff member is required to take at least eighteen hours of workshops per year. We strive to ensure that 100% of our staff are CPR and First Aid certified and that many staff members take a water safety course. Our mission is to have a positive and lasting effect on every child who enters our center. We strive to help children tap into their potential, create happy memories, and develop a positive self image that will guide their future for many years to come.

column2: Little Apples Day Care & Learning Center
column11:
Little Apples is locally owned and operated by the Szelog family since 1993. Located in Hooksett since 1996, Little Apples Day Care & Learning Center strives to enhance positive self worth within the child. Our staff accomplishes this through developmentally appropriate environments and materials. Children are cared for in a loving, nurturing manner, fostering their growth from within.

We care for children ages 6 weeks to 2nd Grade and we are open year round, from 6:30am to 6:00pm. At Little Apples we feel children are unique individuals and are treated as such. Each child is guided through tasks and encouraged to master learning goals independently. 

Our staff members are both care givers and teachers. The role of a teacher is to encourage and guide children towards making positive life choices. Parental involvement is a vital part of Early Childhood Education and parents are encouraged to take part in as many activities as possible. Little Apples has an open door policy, encouraging parents to drop by.

We also feel communication is vital to a child’s success. We have a monthly news letter entitled; APPLESEEDS, as well as a classroom calendar and daily notes.

Our mission at MJECP is to provide families with high quality programs for their children's early learning and development. Within a thoughtfully prepared, warm and caring environment, we will support children's learning through carefully planned activities as well as spontaneous interactions and daily routines. We strive to meet the many diverse needs of today's families, and to be a partner with parents in giving children the best early experiences possible.

Bright Horizons is the world's leading provider of employer-sponsored child care, back-up care, education and work/life solutions with more than 700 child care and early education programs and schools for employers and working families across the US, UK, Ireland and Canada. Committed to creating great work environments for its 18,000 employees, the company has been named 12 times as one of FORTUNE magazine's "Best Companies to Work for in America."

Bright Horizons provides work/life solutions for more than 800 leading employers to help them address challenges across key life stages. Programs include child care, back-up care, college counseling, elder care, and work/life consulting.

The first few years of life are an extraordinary time that sets the stage for all the years that follow. Our program for learning creates educational environments that empower children to be confident, successful, lifelong learners and socially responsible citizens. Bright Horizons' innovative programs help children, families, and employers work together to be their very best.

It is important that every child develop a trust in his/her teachers and others in the early stages of his/her school life. He/she must be able to feel free to express himself/herself verbally. He/she must be able to feel free to cry, to be afraid, to enjoy and to fail without loss of self-respect or loss of acceptance as a person. If he/she is allowed to develop this sense of trust, a sense of autonomy will evolve. As a child feels safe, and is aware of himself/herself as a human being, he/she feels comfortable enough to develop initiative, to test, to explore, to imagine and to accomplish. Children need success in their experiences in order to build confidence and give them faith in themselves and their daily ability to move ahead with new tasks. Successful experiences are vital in building a positive self-esteem. School is a testing ground for children to learn about relationships, sharing, taking turns, and cooperating. It is here that he/she begins to learn to value and defend his/her rights. It is here that he/she begins to learn that life is filled with choices and that with those choices come responsibilities and consequences. Here, he/she will begin to understand his/her own feelings and to appreciate the feelings of others.

We offer a non-competitive environment where the children are encouraged to work according to their own interests and abilities.  Without pressuring the child academically, the child is allowed to develop at his/her own pace, learn the importance of making responsible choices and actively direct his/her own experiences.  Through careful observation, we can monitor a child's learning process and connect them to the appropriate materials when they are ready.  Our goal is to assist the child in developing life skills that will carry them through their adult life.

Thank you for your interest in Learning Adventures Early Childhood Center, we invite you to come and tour our facility so that you may learn more about our offerings for children ages 12 months to 12 years.

Each morning, we welcome up to 35 children and their families into our program, and each day, we have the same goal – to provide every child with a safe, quality environment in which to explore the world around them through meaningful experiences and activities. We believe that childhood should be a journey filled with wonder and discovery and is a time to take notice of the small things that often get overlooked by adults.

By always making a child feel safe, secure and respected, the child will explore and play to make sense of their curious surroundings. These experiences will not only enable a child to become more self-confident, but will also allow them to develop key social, physical, emotional, and cognitive skills that will benefit them throughout their entire lives. This philosophy is expounded by our teachers every day and is the Learning Adventures difference.

The Andover After School Program (AASP)  provides  afterschool childcare for elementary aged children in Andover, New Hampshire.

Our mission is
... to provide a safe, friendly environment for elementary school children with an emphasis on friendship and fun!

Our program is housed in the AEMS Annex (the former “Hamp House”) which creates a warm, welcoming home-like atmosphere for the children.

Here at Watermelon Seeds we encourage students to learn about their world and its many wonders. Using a hands-on approach, we seek to develop creative self-discovery through fostering a child's natural curiosity and love of literature, science, art, music and culture.

We strive to provide your child with a happy, fun-filled learning experience and to help them become peaceful citizens. With our overlying theme of World of Wonder we hope to inspire and excite each child to appreciate all the wonders of their world and their part in the larger world.

Each month, we will take your child on a journey of enlightenment with themes such as The Wonders of You; The Wonders of Art & Music; The Wonders of the Earth; The Wonders of Light; The Wonders of Transportation; The Wonders of the Rainforest; The Wonders of the Farm;  The Wonders of Water and The Wonders of Your Back Yard. At East Andover Village Preschool, we follow an emergent curriculum model which focuses on the children's collective thoughts, ideas and questions about their world.  Our developmental goals and objectives are from Teaching Strategies, Inc. Creative Curriculum Model (http://www.teachingstrategies.com/page/73749-creative-curriculum-preschool.cfm), which is aligned with the NH Kindergarten Readiness Indicators.  Our activities are developmentally-appropriate and meet each child's individual developmental objectives.  Children are given hands-on opportunities to explore their environment and world around them.  Each day there are activities for literacy, mathematics, social studies, science, creative representation and music and movement.    

Our daily schedule offers children many opportunities for social-emotional development through free play and cooperative activities during our morning choice time.  Children are split into primary care groups which allows for more one-on-one experiences between teacher and child. 

Our playground has recently been renovated and new learning areas are continuing to be added to the space.  We have a few garden beds which allow us to follow the Early Sprouts Curriculum.  Through this curriculum children are offered experiences and opportunities to grow, eat and cook with bell peppers, beans, tomatoes, butternut squash, Swiss chard and carrots.  Children will gain the knowledge in taking care of living things along with exploring health, nutrition, and cooking.

Southern New Hampshire Services, Inc. (SNHS) is a private non-profit corporation chartered in the State of New Hampshire, May 21, 1965 to serve as the Community Action Agency for Hillsborough County in compliance with the Economic Opportunity Act of 1964.

From 1965 through 1969, SNHS was known as the Community Action Agency for Hillsborough County and served the City of Nashua and the twenty-nine towns.  In 1969 the organization became the Community Action Agency for the City of Manchester as well.  In 1974 the agency’s name was changed to Southern New Hampshire Services, Inc.

In July, 2011, Rockingham Community Action (RCA), the Community Action Agency serving Rockingham County, was merged with Southern New Hampshire Services.  SNHS had served as the administrative agent for RCA since October, 2008.  As a result of this merger SNHS now provides services to residents all 65 towns and three cities in Hillsborough and Rockingham counties.

The New Hampshire Montessori Association is a non-profit organization, formed in February 2007 to create a forum for the continuing education of Montessori teachers in New Hampshire, and to promote the Montessori philosophy in our state. We are energized by the prospect of reaching out to the Montessori community as well as other educators and parents interested in the work of Dr. Maria Montessori.

In our busy lives and work we must take the time to build connections within our Montessori community. The simple experiences of talking with other teachers, visiting other schools, and participating in workshops rejuvenate us as we are reminded of the core meaning in our work as Montessori teachers, the legacy of Dr. Maria
Montessori’s life. NHMA intends for this website to be a resource for the Montessori teachers of NH as well as a place to share knowledge and gain new perspectives in our ever changing profession.

column11:
The mission of Oz Land Early Learning Center is to educate children intellectually, physically, socially, and emotionally by recognizing individual differences, promoting self-esteem, and fostering respect for others. Our child-centered environment encourages exploration and expression which are essential components to the active learning process. We strive to develop a dynamic, educational partnership among families, Oz Land, and the community that work together to maximize the potential of each child.

We believe that human diversity is integral to the care and education of young children and to all those who touch their lives. Diversity at Oz Land can be defined as "a fully inclusive community that is enriched by persons of different races, genders, ethnicities, nationalities, economic backgrounds, ages, abilities, sexual orientation and gender identity or expression, and religious beliefs." Our goal is to promote awareness and acceptance, affirm equity, and take an active stance against bias in our community.
We strive to respect and value the differences in each child and family in our community through all that we do. We value the development of strong relationships with families and colleagues in order to better understand how we can respond to cultural and historical differences in experiences, values, and practices. We offer an environment that welcomes and celebrates the sharing of family history and culture in the classroom in meaningful ways. In our curriculum we are intentional in providing children with opportunities to explore similarities and variation, and we are responsive to the questions that emerge.

We support children in being active participants in their world by connecting them to their community in ways that foster an understanding of diversity and an ability to effect change. We are committed to an open and ongoing dialogue among colleagues, families, and the students we mentor, seeking insight into how we contribute to social bias and the process of change. As adults we strive to be model: of active participation in our field by speaking out against bias and seeking equity.

column11:
Welcome to St. Paul’s School, a co-educational, fully residential high school founded in 1856. We are an Episcopal school, welcoming of all faiths, made up of approximately 525 students from all over the world. We are a community of students and teachers and families, who live and learn together. We try to live by our School Prayer, which urges kindness and an eagerness to “bear the burdens of others.” St. Paul’s is academically rigorous, but staffed with teachers who take the time to know the whole student, whether in the classroom, in the dormitory, on the athletic fields, or along one of the many paths that wind through the campus. Because high school is such a formative time, most alumni tell us that they made their most enduring friendships at St. Paul’s.

All students and all faculty live on campus, so there is never a shortage of peers to study with or hang around with in the dorms, or adults to provide guidance and support away from home.

It is in this setting that we are able to offer Play Group to 16-20 toddlers per week. Play Group is funded by United Way. It is open to toddlers who are enrolled in Early Supports and Services and who do not otherwise have an opportunity to play with children around their age. OUR SCHOOL DAY is founded on the ideals and practices of early childhood Waldorf education as developed by Rudolf Steiner and is structured to give children the opportunity to learn through movement, imitation and exploration. The teachers provide the routines and rituals of the days, weeks and seasons, allowing for a secure and rich environment for the unfolding of each child.

The day begins with free play. Our simple wooden and handmade toys become whatever the child imagines—puppet shows are performed, bridges and roads are built for trucks, houses and living spaces are made and remade—while the children transform into queens and kings, kittens, cooks, doctors and astronauts.
Holding this space for play, the teachers are engaged in practical activities the children can enter at will: peeling carrots and washing fruit for morning snack, folding napkins for the setting of the table, molding beeswax with warm fingers and felting wool.

The Place to Go, a non-profit organization, offers the state’s only free after-school program, Kids Together, located in Peterborough, NH.  Since 1996 it has provided a safe environment for children in grades 3-8, where they are warmly received and supervised.

The Kids Together program continues to grow, even in these difficult times. We are considered one of the top two (free) programs in the state.  The economic uneasiness that has touched so many of us has hit working families with young children among the hardest.

The Place to Go, Kids Together program supports approximately 40 children representing a cross section of  the Peterborough area population. They meet in three sessions each week.

Some children are referred to the program by school social workers and teachers, while others are latch-key children whose parents cannot be home during after-school hours.

Although the program’s mission as stated in the by-laws is simple: “to provide an after-school care program for children in the greater Peterborough area” – our curriculum actually brings more of a exceptionally rich and more meaningful experience   to the children than they might get elsewhere

column2: Cradle And Crayon Child Development Center
column11:
Cradle & Crayon, Inc. (CCI) operates the CRREL Child Development Center (the Center) under contract with the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers within the Department of Defense (DoD).  The Center provides child development services to families and employees of the Engineer Research and Development Center (ERDC) located at the Cold Regions Research and Engineering Laboratory (CRREL) as well as to members of the local community. It is the only U.S. Army facility with the ability to extend its services to the community through special arrangements as part of the existing contract.  CCI is a non-profit corporation, founded and controlled by a membership consisting of parents of the Center. The Center offers full time day care for children between the ages of six weeks and six years.

​The Center provides a safe and nurturing environment that contributes favorably to the growth and development of children.  The Center strives to meet or exceed the expectations of our parents.  The Center is certified annually by the Department of Defense, holds a New Hampshire Child Care Program License and is accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC).

 The Center retains accreditation by the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC) – a standard that few area centers continue to pursue due to the extensive application and review process.  This includes strict requirements for staff qualifications and training, environment, management, and curriculum, all with the ultimate objective to provide the best support for our children’s learning and development.

It is the goal of FitKids childcare to create and maintain a warm, nurturing environment that supports the naturally paced emotional, social, physical and intellectual growth of each child. In our program, learning is integrated into the daily routine. We believe that playing should not be separate from learning, rather, playing is learning.

Lyme Nursery School is a non-profit, cooperative nursery school whose purpose is to promote the social, emotional, physical, intellectual, and artistic growth of young children. This is accomplished by fostering self-esteem, self-control, respect for others, and a sense of security with both peers and adults. In order to meet the educational needs of young children, the school provides an enriching environment that stimulates learning, imagination, and creative expression, and encourages the development of each child’s communication and problem-solving skills. In addition to the social and academic aspects of our program, LNS places great emphasis on time spent outdoors, helping children to explore the environment and world around them.

column11: SCS Head Start is a NAEYC (National Association for the Education of Young Children) accredited preschool program for children; it is also a family development opportunity for parents and caregivers. Our seven Head Start centers are conveniently located throughout Cheshire and Sullivan counties. Our main office is located at Southwestern Community Services in Keene.  Head Start provides a supportive and consistent preschool educational environment for children and families through open communication, exceptional resources, and positive role modeling to help children and adults become successful and self-sufficient.

Welcome to Little Blessings Child Care Center at Christ Church. We are licensed by the state of New Hampshire. We were the first Center in the state to achieve Licensed Plus status, a designation indicating our above-average service. We operate with a staff of twenty full time and three part time employees, many of whom hold a teacher credential from the state of New Hampshire as well as CPR and First Aid training and extensive training in adult and child sexual misconduct. We meet or exceed all state teacher/child ratios.

Little Blessings Child Care Center operates on the developmental philosophy that all children grow and learn at their own individual pace, not according to a calendar. We recognize the importance of a child’s social, emotional, physical, and intellectual development. We teach the children to respect others as well as themselves. We provide an environment where children can interact with other children as well as with adults. We provide an opportunity to experience the joys of friendship.

At Discovery Child Enrichment Center(DCEC), we strive to provide the hightest quality childcare possible. Children in our care will grow and learn through exploration and positive play experiences. Each child is special and deserves the highest quality care and attention. Our very first priority is always providing a safe and nurturing environment, tailored to meet each child's needs.

Early Childhood Research supports the concept that children learn most effectively when interacting with adults, materials, and the environment in ways that help them make sense of the world. Learning activities and materials should be concrete, real, and relevant to a child’s life, while providing a wide range of complexity and challenge so as to meet each child’s developmental and cognitive needs.

The Project Approach emerges from children’s ideas and interests. Each project allows children the opportunity to question, experiment, plan, sustain interest, work toward long-range goals and develop problem solving skills. Curriculum is naturally integrated as children represent and record their observations and knowledge through art, science, math, language, writing, music and creative play. By working on projects that are meaningful to them, children develop important social skills such as working cooperatively, sharing ideas, listening to others, negotiating compromises, and sharing ownership in the completed project.

A Hallmark of The Children’s Garden is the exceptional creativity that emerges as children are encouraged to explore a wide variety of materials and express themselves in many ways. The school becomes a kaleidoscope of color and texture through displays of children’s work. Each year is unique, as each group of children creates a collective memory of their preschool experience.

column11: Joyful Footsteps Preschool is Christian based program run by experienced, certified teachers.  Children are provided with learning opportunities through play, exploration, and direct instruction.  Children are provided with many opportunities to interact with each other, their teachers, and the rich environment around them.  Local field trips, special events, and class pets are a regular part of the program.  Activities are adjusted to meet individual learning styles and interests.  We offer a two day a week three year old program and a three day week four year old program.  We also offer extended care enrichment for pre-k and kindergarten children.

column11: At the Community Church of Alton After School Program, children in 1st-6th grades enjoy a friendly environment where they can learn, grow, and play.  Children are picked up from the Alton Central School and walk with leaders to the church.  Upon arriving children have a snack time consisting of yummy fruits and vegetables.  Children then have time to work on homework.  We spend the rest of the afternoon playing outdoors.  On rainy days we have many indoor activities for them to explore.  The after school program follows the Alton Central School calendar running from directly after school until 5:30 pm. Call the church office for registration information.

Bartlett Community Preschool is a private, nonprofit community based preschool that has been serving the children and families of the Mount Washington Valley since 1992.

 Our child-centered program provides high quality, developmentally appropriate care and education. We focus on the needs of the child – physical, emotional, social, cognitive, and familial – in a consistent and secure environment.

Our facility has various play activities and learning experiences set up to provide opportunities for children to develop language skills, math and science concepts, and large and small muscle coordination; to discover how things work; to learn about living things, their community, to learn social and self help skills' and to enjoy music, art and dramatic play activities.

column11: Head Start is a national school readiness program that provides comprehensive education, health, nutrition, and parent and community involvement services to children from eligible families in Strafford County, New Hampshire.

Our childcare center was established in 1972 to provide a caring, loving and educational environment for children. A place to spend their days, to be a safe home away from home and where they gain knowledge and confidence. We provide both fulltime and part time classes with preschool, pre-kindergarten or kindergarten included daily. We want to encourage our parents to spend time with their children so this has made our part time child care and preschool program very popular for families that only work part time. We love offering the ability for our parents who are able to take the summer off and spend with their children a guarantee to return during the school year. 

Our child care center focuses on learning, preparing for life, problem solving, decision making and self-help. Learning respect for ourselves, others and the world around us while promoting independent life and communication skills.  These are key elements which contribute to the child’s development, self esteem, confidence and future success in life. 

Our child care center accepts children 2 years and 9 months old and potty trained through kindergarten PLUS before/after school, snow days, early release and summers for children 1st through 4th grade.

We believe that families, teachers, and the learning environment should all work together to support young children's developing fluency in language and emerging literacy skills. Developmentally appropriate displays - print with photos, nursery rhymes, and seasonal displays affords the children many opportunities to talk with each other and with their teachers, to listen, to question, to explore, to read and write for real-life purposes. The environment is designed to support language and literacy. The classrooms are supportive, respectful, and inclusive to families. We welcome and involve families with photos, developmental panels, parent communication boards with current events and volunteer opportunities, and a mail center to send and receive written messages within the program.

Children in Motion, Inc. offers a thoughtfully designed, thematic curriculum, complete with weekly lesson plans, assessments, conferences, portfolios and newsletters for parents to use as a guide.
Children learn social and academic values and skills through hands on play and structured activities in our learning centers. Our classrooms are organized into areas where the children can find toys and materials related by theme, interest, and skill level. These activities and toys can be used independently by the children, or with teacher direction, to introduce, reinforce and enrich skills and concepts which are the foundation of all future learning. Learning environments are an excellent way to individualize the curriculum to meet the varying needs of young children! Further, each classroom recognizes and embraces the changing needs of specific age groups, so projects and lessons are challenging and fun while remaining developmentally appropriate.

Peter Cottontail is a place where young children learn as they play and share experiences with other children.  We foster the physical, social and intellectual development of the child by providing a variety of materials and experiences best suited for each child's needs.  We feel that we can best serve those needs by offering guidance, warmth and encouragement to the child as he or she grows.  

Our staff hopes to create a positive first school experience and help your children feel good about themselves and about school in general.

column2: Dover Children's Center At The Mcconnell Center

column11: My School is an early childhood center located in Dover, NH. We have been serving the seacoast area for 40 years as an established quality center focusing on the project approach to learning.

The Highland Farm Preschool in Dover NH offers a developmentally appropriate curriculum centered around these intertwined areas of development. We strongly feel that these are the bases for skills a child must meet before he/she is ready for a curriculum that emphasizes the teaching of letters, numbers, reading and writing in a structured manner. Our curriculum philosophy is a child interest program versus a teacher-focused style. It is our belief that children learn from what they are interested in. The teachers create rich experiences to support the children’s knowledge, theories, and to expand on “teachable moments.”

CARING, LEARNING, ATTENTION & PLAY!

The programs at Highland Farm Preschool in Dover NH are designed to enhance the development of young children according to their individual needs.
We recognize that each child is a special person and we shall work to maximize his/her social, emotional, physical and intellectual development.
-Highland Farm Preschool Staff

Growing Places sets itself apart through an understanding that the core of early education is in the development of healthy and trusting relationships between children, teachers and parents. Children learn best when there is a strong partnership between home and school. We value open and honest communication, and we work to build nurturing and trusting partnerships with families.

Our teachers see the unlimited potential in each child and recognize the opportunity and responsibility we have to help children build a strong foundation for future success. Growing Places Teachers understand that every moment matters: their interactions are respectful and responsive, validating children’s feelings.

column2: Live And Learn Early Learning Center
column11:
Live & Learn Early Learning Center, of Lee New Hampshire (NH), is conveniently located for accessibility to all Seacoast families. We are staffed by trained professionals that hold an interest in Early Childhood Education. The staff are picked for their dedication to young children and their joy and excitement of the love of learning. Each caring individual is carefully chosen to meet the individual needs of each classroom and brings with them a special gift to share as we all Live and Learn together.

In 1974, Live & Learn started as a dream to enable children to experience an alternative early learning center environment. It began as a Summer based program; and, in June of 1978, Live & Learn became a year round program that services community needs with a multi-program approach. Over the years, the school has developed into a center-based program on a functional 35 acre farm.

Each program at Live & Learn is based on experiential education, which allows children to explore their environment using a "hands on" approach. We give children the opportunity to experience a number of developmentally appropriate activities, both in and out of the classroom. Each program is staffed to meet the particular needs of the classroom. The staff, as well as the director, continually improves their education and understanding of young children through courses, seminars, and lectures within the field.

Live & Learn is accredited by the National Association of Education for Young Children (NAEYC), which holds the highest standards of quality for early learning centers in the nation. Lead teachers are provided a membership of NAEYC and the state chapter NHAEYC. NHAEYC works to promote quality early childhood education for the children of NH by supporting the Early Childhood Profession.

Live & Learn is also accredited by the National Accreditation Commission (NAC) under the National Association of Child Care Professionals (NACCP). Live & Learn is proud to be the only center in New Hampshire that is accredited by this agency.
Live & Learn was the first Nature Explore Certified Outdoor Classroom in the state of NH. This year marks our 5th year being recertified! Follow the link below to learn about the changes we've made over the year! This certification fits with our nature based curriculum and belief in connecting children with nature on a daily basis.

Meals and snacks are provided.  Way To Grow Preschool invites children ages 2-5 to explore, learn and grow in a safe, fun, and happy environment.

Hill’s Home Preschool and Club Kidz, located in Barrington, New Hampshire, offers quality childcare and education for children ages newborn to 6 as well as before and after school programs for children up to age 9.

We provide children a safe and peaceful place so that they may learn, grow and socialize with others in a nurturing environment.

column2: Mud Pies And Make Believe Children's Center
column11: We at Mud Pies & Make Believe recognize that early education is the most vital part of human development. Our teachers are here to create a secure, nurturing, and healthy atmosphere that encourages creativity and individuality. We have designed theme-based programs that encourage your child's learning to be fun. In these programs your child will explore their environment through diverse activities and adventures. It is essential for all involved to feel comfortable in their environment. We encourage parent/teacher communication in achieving our goal: the growth of your happy, healthy child!

Our Philosophy at Hampstead Village Preschool is to provide young children with a well-rounded preschool experience that will provide a solid foundation for future learning. These experiences include activities to promote the development of a positive self-esteem, respect of others and their environment, awareness and respect of God, and age appropriate development.

We believe that children learn best from the experiences and therefore we strive to provide an optimal environment that allows them to explore and learn through hands-on activities.

Parents are encouraged to be active participants in their child's learning experience at Hampstead Village Preschool in any way they are able.

Staff Qualifications: Our teachers are qualified Early Childhood Professionals. Each classroom is staffed by a Head Teacher who has completed all State educational requirements and has demonstrated competency in teaching young children. Additional classroom teachers are hired as needed to enhance our programs. All staff members are trained in CPR and First Aid.

For the past 75 years, we have had the privilege of knowing and nurturing children at our beautiful, expansive location near downtown Exeter, NH.  We hope that the information on these pages guides you through all the offerings available to your young child. Our two-fold goal is to provide outstanding early childhood education as well support busy family schedules with convenient hours that include early morning and evening care.  

 Our bright and colorful classrooms are designed to welcome our young students, many of whom are having their first experience going to school. Our state licensed teachers aim to create an appropriate balance of free play and structured learning for our curious children. 

 We hope that you find it the inspiring place that we know it to be. 

 We look forward to welcoming you to our school soon.
Great Bay Kids’ Company is a non-profit organization dedicated to providing quality early childhood education and school age enrichment programs for children.

The Montessori School of Exeter is a privately owned school which offers early childhood education and child care. Its philosophical foundation is the work of Dr. Maria Montessori, carried forth by educators with specialty study in the Montessori Method. The school was established in 1979 by Meredith Goodrich.

Teacher training is through The Association Montessori Internationale, the American Montessori Society, The Montessori Center of North America and university programs in Early childhood, and Elementary Education. The school operates under licensing rules and regulations of the State of NH.

Classrooms are designed as prepared environments in which the child may interact directly. Through constant observations the teachers assess the needs of their children individually and collectively, and tailor the environment to them. It is through the child’s direct interaction with the classroom that he is encouraged to meet his own needs and feel the inner joy of self empowerment.

The world is our educational environment; it is funneled through the arts and through the sciences at our school. This integrated curriculum is processed by the child through sequence and order as he sorts and classifies the impressions he receives. He learns best by loving and this is the essence of the program.

The Montessori School strives to create a program which minimizes stress in a child’s life and maximizes balance, self-respect and inborn aptitudes. Through cooperative efforts of the school, staff and parents we can give a child a life long gift.

De Colores Children's Center opened in September 1999 and received the Providian Excellence in Child Care Award in 2002.

Our philosophy is to allow children to celebrate their differences, recognize their similarities, and grow in self-esteem and self-worth. Our teachers give equal encouragement to individuality and cooperation.  In this way, each child learns to be an integral and contributing member of the group through the confidence that a strong sense of self and individuality brings.

Art, music and dance are central to our teaching philosophy and provide a means for stimulating and facilitating the learning process. These creative and essential means of expression are integrated into the children's daily experience at De Colores whether through structured lessons and group activity or on an individual basis.

At De Colores we provide children with an introduction to Spanish. Many of the fundamentals we cover are done in both Spanish and English. In addition, Spanish songs, games and poems are incorporated into the children's daily experience, further enhancing their basic understanding of the language.

In addition to fundamentals such as numbers, shapes, and learning days and months, our curriculum is composed of two themed units. During the 2010-11 school year, the ocean filled our days in the first months of school followed by an all-encompassing study of plant life that filled the second part of the year. The children explored various aspects of each theme in a multitude of ways - through stories, art, song and hands-on experience. In the ocean unit, they learned about ocean life, habitats, ecosystems and shore birds. In the plant unit, they learned how plants grow, the parts of the flowers and trees, and ultimately grew a plant of their own. Both units culminated with the creation of a picture book that allowed each child to show what they had learned.

At the end of the school year, we do an in-depth study of a renowned painter. In this unit, we focus on one painter, learning about his or her life and work and the children create artwork. in the artist's style. Artists about whom we have learned in previous years include Picasso, Monet, O'Keefe, Rothko, Klee, Van Gogh and Matisse. This year, the artist we explored was the Spanish painter, Joan Miro. We have had the children take a close look at many of his paintings and through this study they have learned to recognize commonalities that are specific to his work. At the end of this unit, they gained a more tactile understanding of Miro's work by emulating one of his paintings.

At De Colores, seasons, holidays, themes and units are studied in depth through a hands-on and interdisciplinary approach. Life isn't slotted into labeled boxes, rather it is experiential on a multitude of levels. Songs, stories, dance, art, math, writing, and hands-on activities are tied together at De Colores and brought to life through cohesive themes, which, in turn enhance a child's learning experience.

column11:
Appleseeds is the only early childhood program accredited by NAEYC in Exeter, NH. We are one of eight accredited schools in Rockingham County. We provide high quality early childhood education and care while maintaining school hours of 6:30-5:30 (with an open door policy), to accommodate families busy schedules. Our educational programs for infants, toddlers, preschoolers and kindergartners are based upon NAEYC's best practices and are aligned with NH Department of Education’s Early Learning Standards. Our preschool students transition to kindergarten with the foundation they need for their academic success, some as early readers. Approximately 95% of our kindergartners leave our program as successful early readers. We track each child's developmental progress by building individualized portfolios over the course of the year, infants through kindergarten. The portfolios contain samples of the child's work, documentation of developmental accomplishments, photographs, and documentation of curriculum explaining the goals and objectives of the activities with the child's participation in it. These portfolios create a story of the child's experience in the classroom and validate the child's work within the classroom.

Appleseeds successfully provides nurturing and safe environments for all of our students while focusing on building long lasting trusting relationships with each student and their family. The children only transition once a year to their next classroom in large groups so they are able to maintain established friendships and have a sense of security as they move on to their next classroom. We pride ourselves in the longevity of our teachers. 30% of our teachers have been teaching at Appleseeds for over 10 years and 69% of our teachers have been teaching at Appleseeds for over 5 years. Because of the longevity of our teachers, students and their families have a sense of comfort and security as they transition to the next classroom. Children will often bring their work to their past teachers to show their accomplishments to them. There is a true sense of community as you enter the school. Families get to know one another and develop friendships outside of school. The relationships developed between teachers and families last through the years as well. We often hear how unique Appleseeds is when it comes to the atmosphere at our school and sense of community and partnership.
 
Appleseeds has been featured in several articles in the local newspapers for work on giving back to the community.  This includes the in-school lemonade stand our preschoolers hosted for NHSPCA, the collection for the Ladies of Liberty that our kindergarten class organized and our annual drives for the NH Foodbank and WIC.  We are always providing opportunities for students to learn about good citizenship and caring for the community.

Building Block School is a state licensed preschool/kindergarten center. Our teachers are all qualified professionals and our classrooms are setup with modern equipment and supplies to provide a special environment for children. Each program is designed to meet the needs of the individual child. We respect the fact that not all children are ready for the same things at the same time. The individuality of each child is valued and respected.  Early Childhood education is much more than academics. A balance needs to be maintained so that physical, emotional, and social growth is achieved. Children at Building Block School are encouraged to participate, experiment and discover. They learn, play and explore nature in our wonderful outdoor playground and schoolyard which includes a sledding and climbing hill, playground equipment, sand and snow toys, an open mowed field for running and games, and a school garden with active bird feeders. Learning at Building Block School is hands-on. It is achieved through the excitement of exploring, discovering, experimenting, and thorough enjoyment of unique activities. We vibrantly use the arts and many different forms of media along with the joy of learning about great artists and musicians. Learning is also enhanced by nature study, science, music, literature, 'math their way' and 'count on math' programs in addition to a whole combination of language and phonics.

column2: Great Bay Kids' Company - Lincoln Street Sap
Harris Family Children's Center - Phillips Exeter Academy
column11:
The founder of Phillips Exeter Academy defined its mission more than two centuries ago. "Above all," John Phillips stated, "it is expected that the attention of instructors to the disposition of the minds and morals of the youth under their charge will exceed every other care; well considering that though goodness without knowledge is weak and feeble, yet knowledge without goodness is dangerous, and that both united form the noblest character, and lay the surest foundation of usefulness to mankind."

Exeter today continues the commitment to unite knowledge and goodness. It seeks students who combine proven academic ability, intellectual curiosity, and tenacity with decency and good character. At the Academy, exacting inquiry and thoughtful discourse foster the life of the mind, instruction and activity promote fitness and health, and the daily interactions of a residential school nurture integrity, empathy, and kindness. Because learning and growth at Exeter arise from each individual's engagement with others, the richness of education here requires diversity in all its dimensions; students and faculty value the differences they bring to the community they share.

The challenges that students meet at Exeter and the support they receive have a common purpose: to stimulate their development as individuals and as members of society. Exeter seeks to graduate young people whose creativity and independence of thought sustain their continuing inquiry and reflection, whose interest in others and the world around them surpasses their self-concern, and whose passion for learning impels them beyond what they already know.
